fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.interfaces

Interface ModelDescriptionI

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AtomicModelI, CoupledModelI, EventsExchangingI, ModelI, ParentNotificationI, RTAtomicSimulatorI, RTSimulatorI, SimulatorI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AtomicEngine, AtomicES_Model, AtomicHIOA, AtomicHIOAwithDE, AtomicHIOAwithEquations, AtomicModel, AtomicRTEngine, BatterySensorModel, ControllerModel, CoordinationEngine, CoordinationRTEngine, CoupledModel, HIOA_AtomicEngine, HIOA_AtomicRTEngine, Model, MoleneModel, NetworkModel, PortableComputerModel, PortableComputerStateModel, ServerModel, SimulationEngine, Tic_ES_Model, TicModel, WiFiBandwidthModel, WiFiBandwidthSensorModel, WiFiDisconnectionModel, WiFiModel

    public interface ModelDescriptionI
    The interface ModelDescriptionI declares the methods that can be used to get information from simulation models directly or through their simulation engine or any other proxy reference.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2018-05-30

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

      • getDescendentModel

        ModelDescriptionI getDescendentModel(java.lang.String uri)
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        get a Java reference on the object representing a model that is a descendant or the model executing the method.

        Description

        As this method returns a reference on a Java object, it must be used with much care. Models are not callable through RMI, hence it should not be called through RMI (i.e., among components). Also, direct access to the object representing a model should be read-only, as changing the state of the model can interfere severely with the simulation protocol.

        Contract

         pre     uri != null
 pre     isDescendentModel(uri)
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Parameters:
        uri - this model or a submodel URI.
        Returns:
        the model with the corresponding URI.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - to do.

      • closed

        boolean closed()
        throws java.lang.Exception
        return true if the model is closed.

        Description

        A model is closed if it has no imported event. A model can be considered as closed even if it exports events because they can be executed with their exported events not consumed by any other model.

        Contract

         pre    true            // no precondition.
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Returns:
        true if the model is closed (no imported event).
